  "response": "When traveling with a terminally ill parent, consider destinations that offer:\n\n1. Accessibility\n- Wheelchair-friendly locations\n- Easy transportation\n- Close medical facilities\n- Comfortable accommodations\n\nRecommended destinations:\n\nDomestic US Options:\n- Hawaii (relaxed atmosphere, beautiful scenery)\n- Florida (warm climate, many accessible resorts)\n- California (diverse landscapes, medical infrastructure)\n- Arizona (mild weather, peaceful environments)\n\nInternational Options:\n- Caribbean cruise (medical staff on board, multiple destinations)\n- Canada (similar healthcare system, scenic locations)\n- Parts of Western Europe (good healthcare, accessible tourism)\n\nSpecific Considerations:\n- Short travel distances\n- Mild climates\n- Places with quality medical support\n- Low-stress environments\n- Comfortable lodging\n\nPractical Tips:\n- Consult with their doctor before traveling\n- Check travel insurance\n- Pack necessary medications\n- Plan flexible, low-key itineraries\n- Consider potential medical needs\n- Prioritize comfort over adventure\n\nPotential Bucket List Destinations:\n- National Parks\n- Scenic coastal areas\n- Quiet, peaceful locations\n- Family-meaningful places\n\nRemember: Individual preferences and medical conditions will ultimately determine the best destination.",
